SUMMARY:Caitlin Powell: We’ll See About That! (work in progress)
LOCATION:Camden Comedy Club\, 100 Camden High Street\, London
DESCRIPTION:This year\, Caitlin Powell finished a PhD on fascism (yikes) an
 d promptly crashed out – a reasonable response given *it all*. We’ll Se
 e About That! is for anyone who wants to fix the world but can’t even get
  a hold of their landlord. It’s about meal deals\, moon cups\, and the na
 gging feeling that constantly bracing for disaster is getting in the way of
  being a cool fun time. This is a show for the girls\, gays\, theys (and an
 yone with the pattern recognition of a bloodhound). Caitlin Powell is a ‘
 brilliant’ (Jen Brister) and ‘delightfully self-effacing’ (Chortle) r
 ising star on the circuit. They have been a finalist in the Funny Women Awa
 rds\, Chortle Student Comedy Awards\, and LGBTQ+ New Comedian of the Year\,
  and a two-time nominee for the BBC New Comedy Awards. Their podcast Queers
  Gone By has been described as ‘utterly hilarious’ (The Guardian)\, ‘
 laugh-out-loud’ (GQ) and ‘idiotic’ (Men’s Health).\nMore info: http
 s://comedyatlas.app/comedy-atlas/event/caitlin-powell-well-see-about-that-w
 ork-in-progress/
URL:https://comedyatlas.app/comedy-atlas/event/caitlin-powell-well-see-abou
 t-that-work-in-progress/
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
